The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Sourav makes himself available

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Sourav Ganguly has decided to play for Bengal in the East Zone one-day meet which begins in Dhanbad on Saturday. A 14-member Bengal squad was announced after the former India captain expressed his availability for the Dhanbad games. 

Deep Dasgupta will, however, continue to lead the side. Sourav and Sanjib Sanyal have been added to the squad, while Arindam Das, Asok Dinda and Murtaza Lodhgar have been dropped. CAB president Jagmohan Dalmiya was present during the selection meeting. 

Deep also felt that with Sourav back in the side it would be a different outfit. 

The team leaves for Dhanbad on Thursday. 

 THE SQUAD 

Deep Dasgupta (captain), Sourav Ganguly, Rohan Gavaskar, Laxmi Ratan Shukla, Sourashish Lahiri, Manoj Tewari, Subhamoy Das, Avishek Jhunjhunwala, Subhajit Paul, Shib Shankar Paul, Shiv Sagar Singh, Ranadeb Bose, Kamal Hassan Mondal, Sanjib Sanyal. 

Coach: Paras Mhambrey, 

Manager: Samir Dasgupta. 




